      },
      "date": "2012-04-13 03:05:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, approved\n\nFor the benefit of other reviewers - while this is not using the \"portable\" cfs_mutex* functions, all of the uses are for Linux struct inode i_mutex locks, which should correctly be locked/unlocked by Linux functions.\n\nIn any case, all of the code changed is in the \"non-portable\" parts of Lustre anyway (llite, mds, lvfs, obdfilter), and will never become portable, or is already cleaned up in the orion branch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
